*openbox-3.4.2-r4 (08 Jun 2009)

  08 Jun 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openbox-3.4.2-r4.ebuild, -openbox-3.4.2-r3.ebuild,
  +files/openbox-3.4.2-clip-profile.patch,
  +files/rc.xml.clip.admin:
  Support multiple rc profiles, to enable relaxed rc for 
  ADMIN/AUDIT sessions. Add CLIP rc for ADMIN / AUDIT, which 
  is basically the same as the default USER profile, with 
  window resizing / moving enabled.

*openbox-3.4.2-r3 (16 Jan 2008)

  16 Jan 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openbox-3.4.2-r3.ebuild, -openbox-3.4.2-r2.ebuild:
  Add IUSE clip-deps to remove dependency on glib. GRRRR.

*openbox-3.4.2-r2 (21 Nov 2007)

  21 Nov 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openbox-3.4.2-r2.ebuild, -openbox-3.4.2-r1.ebuild,
  files/rc.xml.clip,files/themerc.clip:
  Move to a more spartan configuration, fit for use with maximized 
  VNC viewers : larger borders, no window buttons, no window moving
  by dragging from the border or titlebar.
  
*openbox-3.4.2-r1 (15 Nov 2007)

  15 Nov 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openbox-3.4.2-r1.ebuild:
  Add IUSE clip-deps to remove dependency on gettext.

*openbox-3.4.2 (12 Nov 2007)

  12 Nov 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  openbox-3.4.2.ebuild, +files/openbox-3.4.2-clip-domains.patch,
  +files/rc.xml.clip, +files/themerc.clip:
  Initial CLIP Import. Patch to support XSecurity domains visibility,
  like SWM, and remove default keybindings. CLIP theme based on clearlooks,
  with the proper definitions for security markings. CLIP-specific rc.xml,
  to disable all key bindings, all menu actions and most window actions 
  except for iconify and close.
  Rhhaaaa, I finally got rid of SWM :)
